-- Polish Stocks: Bank BPH, KGHM Polska Miedz Are Active in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-03-06T14:00:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/polish-stocks-bank-bph-kghm-polska-miedz-are-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  declined 1
percent to 2,260.95 at 2:58 p.m. in Warsaw, down for a second
day.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Bank BPH SA (BPH)   rose 0.9 percent to 40.07 zloty,
gaining for the first time in seven days, after the Polish
lending unit of General Electric Co. posted a profit for 2011.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)   lost 3.9 percent to 140.9
zloty, the lowest level in almost two weeks, after Poland’s sole
copper producer said it needs to make at least one acquisition
to achieve its 2018 production target. The metal declined for a
third day on speculation global growth is slowing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
